What may additional dietary protein mean for persons health? Some people believe that consuming more dietary protein can improve overall health. However, there is no scientific consensus on this point. Some research suggests that high-protein diets may have health benefits, such as weight loss and a reduced risk of heart disease. However, other research suggests that these benefits may not be real, and that high-protein diets may actually be harmful to health. More research is needed to determine the effects of dietary protein on health.

What side effects may result from additional dietary protein? There are few side effects associated with additional dietary protein. However, eating too much protein can sometimes lead to dehydration, constipation, and bad breath.

What increases or decrease may happen in a body result from additional dietary protein? If a person consumes more dietary protein than their body needs, the excess protein will be converted to glucose, which can then be used for energy or stored in the body as glycogen.

textDelta: How would you describe active listening on the part of a second grade teacher? Active listening is when a second grade teacher listens attentively to what their students are saying and tries to understand their perspective. They make sure to give students their undivided attention and ask follow-up questions to ensure they are understanding what the student is saying.
